# How to fill this file (do this ONCE per production domain):
#
# 1. Go to https://dashboard.stripe.com/settings/payment_methods
# 2. Enable "Apple Pay" if it isn't already.
# 3. Under "Apple Pay → Web domains", click "Add a new domain".
# 4. Enter your production domain (e.g. benefactor.com).
# 5. Stripe will give you a file named
#       apple-developer-merchantid-domain-association
#    Download it.
# 6. Replace the ENTIRE contents of this file with that downloaded blob
#    (no comments, no whitespace — just the raw token Stripe gave you).
# 7. Deploy. Stripe will fetch
#       https://YOUR_DOMAIN/.well-known/apple-developer-merchantid-domain-association
#    over HTTPS and validate it. Once validated, Apple Pay tile will start
#    appearing automatically in the Stripe PaymentElement on Safari / iOS.
#
# Notes:
# - The path must be served as plain text (Next.js serves files in /public
#   as-is, so this is already correct).
# - Apple Pay does NOT show up on http://localhost — you must test on
#   the deployed HTTPS domain that Stripe has verified.
# - Google Pay needs no domain verification; it appears automatically in
#   supported browsers (Chrome on Android, Chrome desktop with a saved card).
